solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    string reverseParentheses(string s) {
        stack<string> st;
        st.push("");
        for (char c : s) {
            if (c == '(') {
                st.push("");
            } else if (c == ')') {
                string t = st.top();
                st.pop();
                reverse(t.begin(), t.end());
                st.top() += t;
            } else {
                st.top() += c;
            }
        }
        return st.top();
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a stack to build segments; each segment is reversed exactly once when its closing parenthesis is encountered, giving linear time and space.

